title: Ohio man posed as fake PARKING ATTENDANT to sell out entire lot before nearby soccer game made $1600
description: A con artist made $2,000 in just a few hours by posing as a parking attendant and charging $50 a car to people heading to a soccer game. The man was disguised in a fluorescent green vest.

title: Around 120 football stars are addicted to drugs or gambling, figures show
description: The Everton player, 27, revealed in an interview with Gary Neville last Thursday that he had become addicted to sleeping tablets in the wake of childhood trauma.

title: 'Mind-blowing' 3,000-year-old piece of gold jewellery discovered buried in an Essex field
description: A fragment of a torc - a decorative neck ring - was discovered in a field near Mistley on the River Stour. The Bronze Age artefact has now been officially declared as treasure by a coroner.

title: Family of young man left in coma fight hospital trust to stop doctors withdrawing his life support
description: Samantha Johnson, 46, said she was prepared to go to court to prevent medics at St George's Hospital in Tooting, South-West London, from turning off the ventilator keeping her son Andy alive.

title: Half of Brits say mowing the lawn before 9am is unacceptable
description: The poll of 1,000 people showed that Britain is equally divided over what time the lawnmower should be back in the shed on a summer's evening.

title: The Mail's Personal Finance team wins big at prestigious industry awards
description: Rachel Rickard Straus, Editor of The Mail on Sunday's Wealth & Personal Finance section and Money Mail in the Daily Mail, was named Savings Journalist of the Year.

title: Kemi Badenoch puts finishing touches to post-Brexit deal to sign UK up to Indo-Pacific trade bloc
description: The Business and Trade Secretary, Kemi Badenoch, was in New Zealand to sign the UK up to a huge post-Brexit trade deal with a market of over 500 million people.

title: MPs condemn system that has left Armed Forces with an 'limited reserve' of military equipment
description: In a damning report, the Common's defence committee said the 'highly bureaucratic' procurement system had left the UK 'an extremely limited reserve of fighting equipment.

title: MAIL ON SUNDAY COMMENT: Chameleon Starmer must make up his mind on eco-zealots
description: MAIL ON SUNDAY COMMENT: Opposition party leaders have the luxury of being all things to all men.

title: Wimbledon bosses to commission statue of Sir Andy Murray when he retires
description: Chiefs are to commission a statue of Andy Murray. The 36-year-old, who won the Wimbledon trophy in 2013 and 2016, is the only British man to win singles titles at Wimbledon since Perry.

title: Charlie Teo's supporters refuse to accept his exile to China after unsatisfactory conduct finding
description: Charlie Teo's supporters are planning a huge protest to try to keep him practising in Australia after the neurosurgeon was found guilty of unsatisfactory conduct.
